import { Buffer } from 'node:buffer'; // Creates a zero-filled Buffer of length 10. const buf1 = Buffer.alloc(10); // Creates a Buffer of length 10, // filled with bytes which all have the value `1`. const buf2 = Buffer.alloc(10, 1); // Creates an uninitialized buffer of length 10. // This is faster than calling Buffer.alloc() but the returned // Buffer instance might contain old data that needs to be // overwritten using fill(), write(), or other functions that fill the Buffer's // contents. const buf3 = Buffer.allocUnsafe(10); // Creates a Buffer containing the bytes [1, 2, 3]. const buf4 = Buffer.from([1, 2, 3]); // Creates a Buffer containing the bytes [1, 1, 1, 1] the entries // are all truncated using `(value & 255)` to fit into the range 0255. const buf5 = Buffer.from([257, 257.5, -255, '1']); // Creates a Buffer containing the UTF-8-encoded bytes for the string 'tst': // [0x74, 0xc3, 0xa9, 0x73, 0x74] (in hexadecimal notation) // [116, 195, 169, 115, 116] (in decimal notation) const buf6 = Buffer.from('tst'); // Creates a Buffer containing the Latin-1 bytes [0x74, 0xe9, 0x73, 0x74]. const buf7 = Buffer.from('tst', 'latin1');

#include <iostream> #include <vector> #include <cmath> #include <algorithm> #include <numeric> /** * Computes the Softmax of a vector of logits. * Formula: sigma(z)_i = exp(z_i) / sum(exp(z_j)) */ std::vector<double> softmax(const std::vector<double>& logits) { if (logits.empty()) return {}; // 1. Find the maximum value for numerical stability double max_logit = *std::max_element(logits.begin(), logits.end()); std::vector<double> probabilities; probabilities.reserve(logits.size()); double sum_exp = 0.0; // 2. Compute exp(x - max) and the sum for (double val : logits) { double e = std::exp(val - max_logit); probabilities.push_back(e); sum_exp += e; } // 3. Normalize the vector for (double& p : probabilities) { p /= sum_exp; } return probabilities; } int main() { // Example logits (e.g., outputs from a final linear layer) std::vector<double> input = {2.0, 1.0, 0.1}; std::vector<double> output = softmax(input); std::cout << "Probabilities:" << std::endl; for (size_t i = 0; i < output.size(); ++i) { std::cout << "Class " << i << ": " << output[i] << std::endl; } return 0; }

function countdown(seconds, onTick, onComplete) { let remaining = seconds; const timer = setInterval(() => { onTick(remaining); remaining--; if (remaining < 0) { clearInterval(timer); onComplete(); } }, 1000); return () => clearInterval(timer); // returns cancel function } // Usage const cancel = countdown( 10, (s) => console.log(`${s} seconds remaining...`), () => console.log("Done!") );
